SIMPLE: homomorphism
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homomorphism
<hw>Ho`mo*mor"phism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Homomorphous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Same
as <er>Homomorphy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The possession, in one species of
plants, of only one kind of flowers; -- opposed to
<xex>heteromorphism</xex>, <xex>dimorphism</xex>, and
<xex>trimorphism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The possession of but one kind of
larv⟦ae⟧ or young, as in most insects.</def></p>

<p><-- 4. (Math) A special type of mapping of one mathematical set into
or onto another set . . . -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homomorphy</ent>⟦br⟧
